Author: jl777c#5810
Content: coming up with ways to force people to use something doesnt work very well in open source if it costs them more money. they need to want to do it. KMD not forcing monetization for things, but providing valuable tech, makes it the center of a growing ecosystem. Maybe some projects convert 1% to KMD or 10% as a conduit. maybe some are 0%, others are 100%. There is no set rules. Lets assume 10% of the overall ecosystem volume goes through KMD, which is probably not off by more than an order of magnitude. So KMD is not needed for anything other than 5% per year, but yet as all these other projects start arising, KMD benefits. It is like when barterDEX was active. it didnt force people to use KMD, yet 80% or so did
